abstract: Liberal activists have dogged Mr. Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” in a sign of bubbling frustration with his candidacy.
snippet: Liberal activists have dogged Mr. Buttigieg’s high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” in a sign of bubbling frustration with his candidacy.
lead_paragraph: Mayor Pete Buttigieg of South Bend, Ind., faced back-to-back days of protest this week, as liberal activists dogged his high-dollar fund-raisers with calls of “Wall Street Pete,” amid a growing effort by progressives to try to halt his momentum in the Iowa and New Hampshire nominating contests.

headline_main: Pete Buttigieg Is Met With Protests as He Opens His Fund-Raisers to Press

abstract: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
snippet: The Democratic National Committee announced the next set of primary debates. One will be held in each of the early-voting states.
lead_paragraph: Democratic presidential candidates will debate four times in January and February as the party’s opening quartet of nominating contests approaches, the Democratic National Committee said Thursday.

abstract: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
snippet: Ms. Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in a speech about the economy and corruption.
lead_paragraph: Senator Elizabeth Warren, who has ramped up her criticism of her presidential opponents after months of avoiding conflict, issued another rebuke on Thursday in New Hampshire, taking thinly veiled shots at former Vice President Joseph R. Biden Jr. and Mayor Pete Buttigieg, and calling out former Mayor Michael R. Bloomberg by name.

headline_main: Elizabeth Warren Draws Sharp Contrasts With Rivals in New Hampshire Speech
headline_print_headline: In Speech, Warren Sharpens Attacks on Rivals

abstract: A union in Nevada, the third state to vote in the Democratic primary, told presidential candidates that health care, specifically keeping union health care, is what’s on their members’ minds.
snippet: A union in Nevada, the third state to vote in the Democratic primary, told presidential candidates that health care, specifically keeping union health care, is what’s on their members’ minds.
lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — The union member had a pointed question for Elizabeth Warren: “What is your plan to make sure we keep our community health clinic?”

abstract: The president’s campus intervention ignores the bigger threat of anti-Semitism and threatens speech.
snippet: The president’s campus intervention ignores the bigger threat of anti-Semitism and threatens speech.
lead_paragraph: Last year, anti-Semitic attacks killed more Jews around the globe than in any year in decades. Worshipers were gunned down during Saturday services at Pittsburgh’s Tree of Life Synagogue. Attackers took the lives of a Jewish college student in California and a Holocaust survivor in France. German Jews were cautioned not to wear skullcaps or Stars of David on the street.

abstract: Public opinion has shifted about impeachment, but not about the president. Here’s what that means.
snippet: Public opinion has shifted about impeachment, but not about the president. Here’s what that means.
lead_paragraph: Picture this: a president enjoying the lowest unemployment rate in decades and a booming stock market. He is about to notch a major legislative victory with the passage of a significant trade deal, has appointed two Supreme Court justices and has signed a major tax bill into law. Most voters say they’re better off financially than when he took office, according to polling this week.

abstract: Mr. Biden would roll back President Trump’s immigration policies but would not decriminalize unauthorized border crossings, in contrast with his progressive rivals.
snippet: Mr. Biden would roll back President Trump’s immigration policies but would not decriminalize unauthorized border crossings, in contrast with his progressive rivals.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Joseph R. Biden Jr. on Wednesday released an immigration plan that calls for undoing President Trump’s policies and acknowledges “pain” caused by deportations that occurred during his time as vice president, but does not endorse the decriminalization of unauthorized border crossings, a contrast with more progressive rivals such as Senators Bernie Sanders and Elizabeth Warren.
